{
  "stem": "7177.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we would always go together with a lot of special things.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then the next-- the next brother, Joseph, he was called 'little brother.' Everybody called him [NON-ENGLISH], which is 'little brother.' A genius, unbelievable smart, top of the class.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He now speaks seven languages, but at the time, he only spoke three or four.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was unbelievable smart.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now he would probably go to, you know, whatever schools were the best for him.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But we didn't have too much of a choice where to go to school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But he did get a very good education.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I'll just gave you an example.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When he finally-- before he did his final in this particular school, there were eight possibilities that he did not have to take an oral exam, that he could only do the written exam.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he, he didn't have to do seven written-- oral exams, because he did so well in everything else.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he was always there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the only thing that it did to me, he was-- it-- it hindered me because I tried so hard to catch up with him.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But it never worked.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He was always the smart one.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And he-- if my mother would say, why don't you help Betty with her algebra, because it was not my favorite, then he would say, Mama, she is so dumb.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And maybe teachers at the time were not maybe psychologists or anything like that, But they would always say to me, or very often say to me after a test, they would say, very good test, Betty.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Very, very good test.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Not as good as your brother, but a very, very good test.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I know that it stayed with me all my life.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
